other_tests.findings: Visual acuity was NLP in the right and count fingers in the left for case 1; count fingers in both eyes for case 2; NLP in the right eye and 20/40 in the left for case 3. Fundoscopic examinations showed normal optic disks for case 3 and several microaneurysms for case 2.
other_tests.changes_over_time: In case 1, visual acuity improved to 20/400 in the right eye and 20/50 in the left one year after surgery. In case 2, visual acuity improved to 20/20 in both eyes six months after surgery. In case 3, visual acuity improved to 20/60 in the right eye and 20/25 in the left six months after surgery.
